metadata.name: contrapuntos #351
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodr√≠guez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: Desert Solitude #60
metadata.description: "Desert Solitude" is an exploration of my love for crystals, architecture, being one with nature, escaping technology and becoming ok with the idea of being alone. The series was derived using diffusion Ai models and put together in a generative image composition on fx(hash) May 2022. 123 editions were made available.

metadata.name: Itching for a Glitching #11
metadata.description: A trippy generative animated pattern dances between the corners of the background. Simple generative shapes are placed in the foreground. These shapes modulate and mutate the background while creating a composition and form unique to each piece. The piece represents the cyberpunk ethos using technology to interact with and change the world around us.

metadata.name: miniGlyph #176
metadata.description:
In celebration of #tezos4tezos I am releasing this mini version of a more complex work in progress. 

Every 24th mint (ex: 1, 24, 48, 72, etc) will receive a free physical woodcut.
https://alleditions.art/p/miniglyph

This project is designed such that it can export a layered vector SVG that can be used for plotting or cutting out of wood with a laser or paper with a Cricut.

Shift P - Export a PNG
Shift S - Export an SVG
Shift E - explode the layers

metadata.name: Urban skyline #33
metadata.description:
"The ragged skyline of the city resembled the disturbed encephalograph of an unresolved mental crisis." [J.G. Ballard]

The work presents the abstraction of an architectural skyline with a sail structure in the foreground rotating around its vertical axis and a background of skyscrapers. Colors are assigned through a limited number of selected palettes.

metadata.name: Reading a book #818
metadata.description:
The formal structure of a book is beautiful by itself, but its aesthetic is the tacit atmosphere within which events take place in a story.

The WebGL real-time animation sets up an initial grid based on the fxhash. The grid cells get subdivided into another grid and the resulting cells become filled with pixels in color (~33%) or black and white (~66%).
The colored pixels come in 3 different coloring styles.
- Big Palette (~49%)
- Small Palette (~49%)
- Monochrome [b/w] (~2%)
4 noise algorithms modify the pixels of selected grid cells while at the same time 4 reset algorithms reassemble the initial image. The selected cells switch over time.
